</p>
<p>The appropriate wording for a condolence message depends greatly on your relationship with the deceased and the bereaved.  While formality is often observed, sincerity is paramount.  Avoid clichés or platitudes that might sound insincere.  Instead, focus on expressing genuine sympathy and offering practical support where possible. Remember to keep your message concise and heartfelt, focusing on your fond memories of the deceased if appropriate, and always maintaining a respectful and comforting tone.</p>
    

      <h2 id="heartfelt-condolence-messages-for-family">Heartfelt Condolence Messages for Family</h2>
